  "name": "Ashen Glaive",
  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<img src=\"Art%20-%20Items/weapons/glaive_ashen_black_polearm_ghostly.webp\" /><p>Forged during the Shining Crusade, this ash-colored glaive not only ignores the insubstantial nature of incorporeal creatures but also strikes undead with devastating power. It is said to be forged from the smoldering ruin of a greater lich destroyed by the holy fire of Arazni herself.</p><p>The item appears as a smoking black glaive but feels cool to the touch. In the hands of a skilled wielder, it can be commanded to \"burn\" into the form of a tattoo depicting a thin line of smoke and fire from their hand to their shoulder and it can reside there until called.</p><p>It to function as +1, keen, ghost-touch, and undead bane.</p>",
      "instructions": "",
      "unidentified": "<p>A glaive is composed of a simple blade mounted on the end of a pole about 7 feet in length.</p>"
    },
